# Commit message template — ZarishSphere
# Format: <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# TYPE — choose one:
#   feat      new feature
#   fix       bug fix
#   docs      documentation only
#   refactor  code change, no feature or fix
#   chore     build, CI, dependency update, config
#   standard  new/updated standard entry (ZI-UID)
#   data      data or schema change
#   adr       architecture decision record
#
# SCOPE — choose one:
#   platform | index | standards | fhir | engine | console
#   marketplace | builder | forms | sdk | cli | api
#   note | infra | docs | ci | config | auth
#   health | education | logistics | protection | wash | nutrition
#   dotfiles
#
# SUBJECT:
#   imperative: "add" not "added" · no period · max 72 chars total
#
# EXAMPLES:
#   feat(forms): add MUAC screening form from ZI-HEALTH-00234
#   fix(fhir): resolve patient ID collision in FDMN registry
#   docs(adr): record ADR-003 go-native-fhir-server decision
#   chore(dotfiles): fix PATH duplication in dot_bashrc
#   standard(index): add 12 ILO convention entries to ZI-LABOUR
# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# BODY (optional — blank line after subject):
# Explain WHY. Reference ZI-UIDs, ADR numbers, issue numbers.
#
# FOOTER (optional):
# Closes #<issue>
# Refs: ZI-HEALTH-00234, ADR-003
# BREAKING CHANGE: describe what breaks and migration path
# ---------------------------------------------------------------


